mong those who stayed back until the flood assumed unbearable dimension before they attempted to flee with boat. As at the time of filing this report, the bodies of the victims were yet to be recovered, although local divers were said to have intensified search for the bodies. Vanguard News Nigeria. A non-governmental organisation, DICKENS Sanomi foundation, Friday, rescued 12,300 persons trapped in the ravaging flood in six local government areas in Delta State under its Project ‘Rescue 10,000 Flood victims in Delta and Bayelsa States’. October 20, 2012 In "News" Although, God, in the union of man and woman, admonished that no man (read nobody, force or power), should put asunder what He has joined; the unending flood ravaging the country appears not to be obeying the binding biblical injunction, as it has put asunder the South-South geo-political zone. October 28, 2012 In "Special Report" Horror came in the shape of suicide in one of the resettlement camps in Kogi State where two victims of the ravaging floods decided to take their own lives. They could not bear the loss of properties. Suicide they wrote. In relief camps in Kogi, 20 people have already died.… October 7, 2012 In "Just Human"